		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />He doesn't even need to hack up old games. (if you mean hack up as in destroy like what most reproduction services do and not just rom hacking which I did.) Tetris is MMC1, so he can just buy one of these: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath=24&amp;products_id=43">http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.ph ... ucts_id=43</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />one of these: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath=24&amp;products_id=37">http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.ph ... ucts_id=37</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />and the eproms and capacitors the board needs. He may not even need a case, he can open up the Tetris case and swap the boards for the few minutes the hacked rom will be run, then swap the boards again and the old game will be as it once was.

		

