		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A red PCB isn't very stealthy.
<br />Edit: Scratch that, you don't see the PCB when you look at the connector edge.  But you can see a full set of pins, unusual for a Tetris game.  And it also looks subtly different from a real game, the cartridge edge is whiter and looks thicker, but you'd need to be looking for it to see it.

		

